KZN advocate, Addelaid Ferreira Watt, dies after a bizarre gun incident in court. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - An investigation has been launched into the death of senior state advocate, Addelaid Ferreira Watt. Watt died in a bizarre gun accident at Ixopo regional court on Monday. Brigadier Jay Naicker says the accident occurred when a loaded gun accidentally fell and set itself off. The gun was displayed as evidence during a house robbery case. The family has requested that their privacy be respected.